President Barack Obama granted the CIA a waiver on providing proof that intended targets of drone strikes posed an imminent threat to the US ahead of planned drone strikes in Pakistan .
Dr Warren Weinstein, 73, a 73-year-old economic adviser from the US, and an American aid worker Giovanni Lo Porto, 39, were killed in a botched drone strike in Pakistan in January .
The CIA was seeking to destroy an al Qaeda compound in Pakistan when the two hostages were killed .